Usage

	ctree [-fstuv] [-rname] filename1 [filename2 [filename3 ...]]


Options

    -a: print out all roots in tree
    -d: maximum tree depth (-d# or -d #)
    -f: functions found table (only)
    -n: notify user when complete
    -r: name following will be at top of tree table
    -s: sort the namelist
    -t: print tree table
    -u: functions used table printed
    -v: verbose option
    -x: exclude multiple uselist entries


Explanation

    ctree prints out a tree of functions used by the C files (default).  It
	can also print out lists of the functions used by each function and just
	a list of functions defined in the files.

    The ctree program was compiled with Aztec C on an A3000 with the following
    options: CCOPTS=-qf -wp -c2 -f8.

